The Niger Police Command has arrested one Abubakar Turuwa of Pissa village of Borgu Local Government Area for allegedly killing his father, Turuwa Ibrahim, over sharing of cattle. Commissioner of Police in Niger, Mr Dibal Yakadi, made the disclosure in an interview in Minna on Saturday. He said upon interrogation the suspect confessed to the crime, alleging that his father showed partiality in sharing his cattle between him and his brother. Yakadi stated he used his machete to inflict injuriesÂ  on his father that led to his death. He said that the suspect would soon be charged to court after investigation into the matter. The Commissioner of Police appealed to residents of the state to volunteer useful information on happenings in their communities for the maintenance of law and order. NAN